  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project to Contribute to National Preparedness and Response Efforts to the COVID-19 Outbreak in Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project proposes to address the humanitarian concerns presented by the COVID-19 pandemic related to camp coordination and management, and water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) in Ethiopia. The proposed interventions target internally displaced persons living in congested and unsanitary collective sites, spontaneous and unplanned sites/dispersed settlements, and areas of return. In particular, the scope of the project will be the mitigation of COVID-19 spread in sites through support of government sites management on infection prevention and control, and risk communication and community engagement. In addition, WASH interventions are targeting schools and health posts in areas of significant internal displacement and improving access to adequate water, sanitation and hygiene facilities and awareness of good hygiene practices to improve COVID-19 prevention measures in vulnerable communities.</narrative>
  </description>
